The article is a transcript of a press briefing by the White House Press Secretary. The briefing covers a range of topics including the FCC voting to modernize the E-Rate program, the President's support for comprehensive immigration reform, the Israeli airstrikes on Gaza, financial stability in Portugal, the President's thoughts on LeBron James' decision to go back to Cleveland, the Republican lawsuit against the President, gun violence in Chicago, the strained relationship with Germany, and the Employment Non-Discrimination Act. The briefing also includes the week ahead schedule for the President.